{
  "stem": "15962.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was not enough space to be even under the tent, under the protection of the tent.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was extremely crowded.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were no blankets and no food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were occurrences preceding our-- our stay, just a few days where it's claimed that the Germans, not the Allies, dropped a bomb on the camp and that people were actually eating human flesh, out of desperation.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this-- this happened a few days before we arrived there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We do-- I do recall that one of the air raids, which we watched or saw on the horizon, an American Flying Fortress was shot down.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we could see parachutes floating down and armored vehicles going down into the woods.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were later told that the fliers were shot, that the Germans killed them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, this seemed like a very long time to be in these conditions.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And several of the original boys were still hanging together, always trying to form a group, reform groups, so that we would feel a little bit protected.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because by now, the major nationality in this particular camp were Hungarian Jews that were coming.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of them fresh from their homes in Hungary, because the Germans left the Hungarians alone for a long time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And only towards the end of the war, many of them were sent to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were exceptions.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were actually a large contingent of Hungarian transports that were sent to the gas chambers in the mid-1944, as well.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because nationalities tended to protect each other against the other and gain advantages, whether it was blankets or a dry spot in the tent.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was-- unfortunately, in these extreme conditions, human beings don't always behave like gentlemen.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
